The attack was on Mumbai, the financial heart of the country but the tremor/terror was felt through out the nation. Back in college then, I rememeber seeing one of my friends sitting in front of the TV at a stretch for a long time. Unfortunately her elder sister was in Mumbai then with her office located at Nariman point. Due to the attack, the whole city was in a chaos and all sorts of communication services were rendered unavailable. Her sister was not available on any channel and she was in a state of shock the whole time until she could reach her sister. Such a horrifying feeling. We all could feel it too. The stories, the tales, the news is still so fresh in our minds..

"Shams Sir - that Rubber Boat or Speed Boat is called a Dinghy.  It is inflatable and usually folded up and kept for emergencies in all boats. If the main ship is sinking or damaged, they quickly inflate this boat, attach the engines which is stored alongside food, water, fuel, biscuits etc and other basic necessities. Then it is lowered into water and used to quickly reach ashore. Also, big boats cannot dock anywhere and cannot enter shallow waters. But a dinghy / speed boat can come right upto the beach and onto the sand without any problems. Speedboat doesn't need oars too and fairly easy to control, like a motorbike. 

Also, the story after they enter India waters is slightly different in my opinion. Here is what happened - 
Only a very limited type of Fish enter India Markets, like Bangda, Surmai, Poplet etc. Fishes which are quite small is preferred by Indians as most of our recipes calls for such fish, either fry or curry. If it is big, the fish gets sliced into steaks and used but Indians don't like fishes bigger than your hand and prefer small fishes, no bigger than a couple of feet, this is what is sold in markets, easy to store too. Big fish is simply to expensive to store and people don't like to buy chunks, they want the entire fish. Freshness of fish can be determined by looking at its eyes and gills and these big 5 feet, 10 feet fish has no takers. Now, why I am talking about Fishes? because when Fishermen from India catch big fishes like a Marlin or Tuna, they send it abroad, i.e. export it. For e.g. Tuna is highly popular in Japan and not so much in India plus they got higher price for it. So, when Fishermen catch big size fish, they send it off to Dubai and other middle-east markets as they get good returns for it.  

The eating style in the middle east region is community style. You must have seen videos of entire goat or camel being buried underground and steamed/roasted. It is served on a big platter on top of rice and people sit around it and eat together. That is why Big Fishes are in demand there as it can be served as a whole. Of course, sometimes it is sent to fish packing industries where it is canned etc. OK, enough with the fishes, i will get to the point i am making. 

Middle east traders have contact details of many Indian fishermen for the reason described above. Fish has to be consumed fresh so they have financed many Indians with better boats, including faster engines, Honda, Yamaha engines are very popular, lot of horse power. They are costly too and not readily available. But in Dubai and other middle eastern nations, it is quite easy to get these type of engines. So, Indian Fishermen and Dubai Traders are in constant touch on a daily basis and carry out many business deals. Good money is involved so its been going on for a few years. Now, the main planner of this attack used this and contacted his Dubai friends and obtained contact details of Indian Fishermen. They speak with the captain of Kuber and make a deal before hand itself and ask him to come to the designated spot at so and so time for transport of some fish or some other commodity. They don't tell they are moving terrorists and treat this as a business deal promising money, engines, commodities from Dubai etc. 

10 + boat crew of al-huseni enter the start of India waters without any problems as ships in international waters don't get checked by Authorities. At agreed spot find an Indian registered fish boat, Kuber. This is called a Trawler boat and and fairly common as its used by most fisherman from Guj and Maharastra.  Both boats come side by side and 10 people enter Kuber, kill the crew, spare just one person as they need directions to reach Mumbai. Impossible to navigate in sea waters unless you have spent many years on the sea, that too in the night, they have to navigate using stars. These 20-22 old did not have maritime experience. Even if Coast guard or Navy see this Trawler, they will not bother as they will conclude it belongs to some fisherman and used for fishing.  

When they are near the coast of Mumbai, they use that Dinghy or speed boat and kill off that last indian fisherman, get on that speed boat and make way for the coast and stop that Dinghy, in pitch dark right on the beach, pull it ashore and dump it there. Not a drop of water on them. Locals do see this but don't do much as they have seen this before. Gold , Drugs and lot of things get smuggled and its controlled by gangs. Locals do not interfere with Gangs for fear of their life. As long as they don't bother the locals in any way, it is permitted and this is happening for the longest time. Especially in the 80s, Gold smuggling was at its peak and locals themselves were used to load/unload the boxes from boats to vans etc. Some locals call 100 and report to police but cannot describe the problem accurately. They see teenagers with large bags and assume it to be some sort of drug deal or some one doing import/export business etc. They don't have the foggiest idea that these are Terrorists and are here to kill them all. 

After the beach, they reach the road and here is where they meet their Indian Handler! this is not revealed by anybody but i am sure Indian Handlers are involved in this operation. Mumbai Taxi Drivers do not take passengers that easily and that too when not talking the local language. Indian Handler(s) were there, they were given instructions before hand that some people are coming at this time and they need to get to the city in some hotel. So, the Indian Handler arranges for a few taxis and is waiting at the spot for their arrival. When they come, he guides them into the taxis and leaves from there. Indian Handler too has no idea that this is a terrorist attack. They think this is some gangster, drugs, gold or some illegal thing. They don't ask questions too as they know they will get wrong or incomplete answers. Besides if police get hold of them, they will torture them to high hell and reveal all info. So, without complete knowledge, Indian Handler with orders from his bosses in Dubai or Saudi, help 10 people to get into 5 taxis and gives instructions to Taxi Drivers to drop them off, Shivaji Stations, Taj, Cama Hospital etc etc. Fare is pre-paid already so 2 people sit in each taxi without bothering about anything. With 1000s of taxis in Mumbai, police have no clue either. If they had used a Van or 7 seater white board vehicle, there are chances that cops will stop them but taxis, that too 2 people and in trendy clothes, nobody will suspect a thing."

This is a request that recently US officially accepted authenticity of video of unidetified flying object recorded by camera onboard us fighter plane. Earlier it was very widely covered by tv series named ""unidentified"". But it is very poor thing to know that there is hardly any quality content in hindi covering this topic. 
I request you kindly prepare a detailed series on it not only summarising amazing information revealed in series ""unidentified"" but also the sightings of ufo in himalyas which is many times confirmed by Indian soldiers. Please do cover other confirmed sightings in India which were recorded and have conclusive evidences. Details of various such incidence along with recorded pictures and videos are available on internet but all this information is scattered. There are also dozens of incidents when commercial pilots have confirmed these sightings. Plenty information is also available on wikipedia. Can you please collect it and produce a series of episodes on this topic.
Pls, if you are doing it then do it only for incidents which have either strong recorded evidence or witnessed by very large number of people. Pls do not include hoaxes and fake content and denying them at end of programme because there is also a huge stockpile of such fake stories too on internet. They only take away people's interest from authentic stories.
Thank you."
